question_title: Will the interest in “government shutdown 2026” change between 2026-02-02 and 2026-02-12 according to Google Trends?
summary: Google Trends interest in "government shutdown 2026" is currently elevated because we're IN an active partial shutdown (started Jan 30-31, 2026). The shutdown is expected to resolve by Feb 4 when the House passes funding. However, DHS funding expires on Feb 13, creating another deadline just one day after the measurement date (Feb 12). The key dynamic is that Feb 2 captures peak shutdown interest while Feb 12 will capture pre-deadline interest. Being in an active shutdown typically generates more searches than approaching a deadline, favoring "Decreases." But the tight ±3 point threshold makes "Doesn't change" quite plausible if both dates have similarly elevated interest around their respective events.

factors.description: Feb 2 is during an active partial shutdown (day 3-4) while Feb 12 is before a deadline but likely no shutdown - being IN a shutdown generates more searches than approaching one
DHS funding expires Feb 13, one day after Feb 12 measurement - creates pre-deadline search interest on Feb 12
Shutdown expected to resolve by Feb 4 - interest will drop during Feb 5-10 period between measurements
Tight ±3 point threshold means even modest changes in either direction register as change - both dates at elevated levels (40-50 range) could easily be within threshold
Senate Majority Leader Thune expects contentious DHS negotiations and multiple CRs - could increase Feb 12 interest as deadline approaches without resolution
